        "Water"
    ],
    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Tip: If using an air fryer, preheat the <strong>air fryer</strong> to 160\u00b0C/180\u00b0C!</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Higgidy spinach feta pie[s]</strong> to one side of a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 10-12 min</p><p>Tip: If using an air fryer, remove all packaging (including the foil tray) and bake your pie[s] for 15-20 mins or until golden brown and piping hot throughout!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a large splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the Tenderstem broccoli to form a tightly sealed parcel[s]</p><p>Tip: Cooking your pie[s] with an air fryer? Add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to a pot and cover with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>waxy potatoes </strong>to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the pie[s] have had an intial 10-12 min, add the <strong>foil parcel[s]</strong> to the other side of the baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for a final 10-12 min or until the Tenderstem broccoli is tender with a slight bite and the pie[s] is golden and cooked through</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fork tender, drain the potatoes and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong> to the pot with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>garlic butter potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-greek-feta-and-spinach-pie-with-garlic-butter-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Higgidy spinach feta pie</strong> with the <strong>garlic butter potatoes</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
